@spec tm_cc_gating_spec  src=tests/specs/tm_cc_gating_spec.lua  loc=155  sha=751e7cb  cases=4
@exercises midiManager (h.fm), dataStore (h.ds), trackerManager (h.tm)
@surface   fm:dump, ds:assign, tm:fromLogical, tm:addEvent, tm:flush, tm:getChannel, tm:assignEvent, tm:deleteEvent
@harness   mk{seed.ccs}

# Intent
  Phase A of the dirt spine (design/archive/dirty-channels.md § Scheme): the CC walk's timing
  reconcile is gated per dirty channel. A clean channel is converged (raw agrees with its
  logical projection), so skipping it stages nothing -- but a swing change must still reseat
  the channels it resolves to. That dirt is config, not carried by the mm reload payload, so
  markSwingStale must feed the spine or the gate wrongly skips the reseat. This pins that.

# Helpers
  @fn ccRaw(h)  @ 12-14
  @fn note(chan, ppq, pitch)  @ 16-19
  @fn ccMmBag(h)  @ 22-32
      -- cc/at/pc mm records minus the volatile per-rebuild loc: a reseat assign churns this bag.

# Cases
  @case 'swing change reseats a CC through the dirtyChans gate'  [harness]  @ 36-58
  @case 'a note edit carries the cc columns untouched and stages no cc mm write'  [harness]  @ 61-91
  @case 'a cc assign re-clones only its own cell; siblings and other rows carry'  [harness]  @ 94-118
  @case 'a cc add and a cc delete splice their own column only'  [harness]  @ 121-153

# Uses (outbound edges)
